SIMPLE: funeral
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Funeral
<hw>Fu"ner*al</hw> <pr>(f⟦umac⟧"n⟦etil⟧r*⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[LL. <ets>funeralia</ets>, prop. neut. pl. of <ets>funeralis</ets>
of a funeral, fr. L. <ets>funus</ets>, <ets>funeris</ets>, funeral: cf.
F. <ets>fun⟦eacute⟧railles</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The solemn
rites used in the disposition of a dead human body, whether such
disposition be by interment, burning, or otherwise; esp., the ceremony
or solemnization of interment; obsequies; burial; -- formerly used in
the plural.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>King James his <qex>funerals</qex> were performed very solemnly in
the collegiate church at Westminster.</q>
<rj><qau>Euller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The procession attending the burial of the dead; the
show and accompaniments of an interment.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The long
<xex>funerals</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A funeral sermon; -- usually in the plural.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Mr. Giles Lawrence preached his <qex>funerals</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Funeral</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Funeral
<hw>Fu"ner*al</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL. <ets>funeralis</ets>. See
<er>Funeral</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>Pertaining to a funeral;
used at the interment of the dead; <as>as, <ex>funeral</ex> rites,
honors, or ceremonies</as>.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Funeral pile</b></col> <it>or</it> <col><b>Funeral
pyre</b></col></mcol>, <cd>a structure of combustible material, upon
which a dead body is placed to be reduced to ashes, as part of a funeral
rite; a pyre.</cd></cs></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Fu"ner*al*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark></wordforms> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>funeral home</ent>⟦br⟧
